HEADWORD: Unbidden
<hw>Un*bid"den</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Not bidden; not
commanded.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thorns also and thistles it shall bring thee forth⟦br⟧
<qex>Unbid</qex>; and thou shalt eat the herb of the field.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Uninvited; <as>as, <ex>unbidden</ex>
guests</as>.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Being without a prayer.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unbind</ent>⟦br⟧
